We conducted a May 6th to 20th, 2025, 

🧠 5.2.1. Topic Interpretation Evaluation Methodology

We employed two complementary approaches to evaluate topic quality:

    Human Assessment

    Automated LLM Evaluation
    (using Deepseek R-1, Google Gemini 2.5 Pro, and ChatGPT o3)

📝 Evaluation Design

    Five topics per model were selected using coherence score stratification:

        Highest

        Upper Quartile (Q3)

        Median

        Lower Quartile (Q1)

        Lowest
        This ensured a balanced representation of topic quality.

    Each topic was evaluated on two criteria using a 1–5 Likert scale:

        Interpretability: Clarity and coherence of topic themes

        Relevance: Connection to Long COVID discourse and experiences

⚠️ Notes on BERTopic

Due to the large number of granular topics produced by BERTopic, interpreting individual topics consistently was more challenging. This factor was taken into account when analyzing comparative results.

